'''Asafo Market''' is a trading centre in Asafo, [[Kumasi]], the capital of [[Ashanti Region|Ashanti]], to the western side of the [[Asafo Interchange, Kumasi|Asafo interchange]]. Asafo Market was formerly called Nkrumah Market, which was named after the first Prime Minister of Ghana, [[Kwame Nkrumah]], but the name was changed to Asafo Market when Nkrumah was overthrown.<ref name="Kumasi Metropolis Tourism Attractions">{{cite web|url=http://www.kma.ghanadistricts.gov.gh/?arrow=atd&_=6&sa=581 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150925134913/http://www.kma.ghanadistricts.gov.gh/?arrow=atd&_=6&sa=581 |dead-url=yes |archive-date=25 September 2015 |title=Kumasi Metropolis Tourism Attractions |work=[[Kumasi Metropolitan Assembly]] |publisher= |date= |accessdate=2 August 2015 }}</ref>
