'''Edvardas Adamkavičius''' (March 31, 1888 – May 10, 1957) was a [[Lithuanian people|Lithuanian]] general. He was born in [[Pikeliai]], [[Telšiai County]], Lithuania. He enlisted in the [[Lithuanian Army]] in 1918. He was made a [[lieutenant general]] on September 6, 1933, a [[brigadier general]] in 1936 and a [[divisional general]] on February 16, 1937. He retired in 1940. After the occupation of Lithuania by the [[Soviet Union]], he fled to [[Germany]]. He immigrated to the United States in 1949. He died in [[Worcester, Massachusetts]]. He was the uncle of future [[President of Lithuania]], [[Valdas Adamkus]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Bartasevičius|first1=Valdas|title=Vyties Kryžiaus kavalieriai istoriją rašė narsa ir krauju|url=http://kultura.lrytas.lt/istorija/vyties-kryziaus-kavalieriai-istorija-rase-narsa-ir-krauju.htm|website=lrytas.lt|accessdate=July 20, 2017|date=March 29, 2014}}</ref>
