{{for|an earlier publication of the same name|Gazeta Basarabiei (1923)}} {{Infobox newspaper | name = Gazeta Basarabiei | logo = | image = | caption = | type = | format = | owners = | founder = | publisher = | editor = [[Ion T. Costin]] | chiefeditor = V. Boldescu | assoceditor = | maneditor = | newseditor = | managingeditordesign = | campuseditor = | campuschief = | opeditor = | sportseditor = | photoeditor = | staff = | foundation = 1935 | political = | language = [[Romanian language|Romanian]] | ceased publication = 1940 | headquarters = [[Chișinău]] | circulation = | sister newspapers = | ISSN = | oclc = | website = }}
'''''Gazeta Basarabiei''''' ({{lang-en|Bessarabia Gazette}}) was a newspaper from [[Chișinău]], [[Bessarabia]], founded in 1935.<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20120304035846/http://www.hasdeu.md/ro/ebibl/poslednij.pdf PRESA BASARABEANĂ de la începuturi pînă în anul 1957. Catalog] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120304035846/http://www.hasdeu.md/ro/ebibl/poslednij.pdf |date=March 4, 2012 }}</ref>
==Overview==
Between 24 October and 17 November 1923, Gazeta Basarabiei was a weekly of the [[Romanian National Party]], edited by [[Ion Pelivan]] and [[Constantin Mâțu]].<ref>[[Constantin Mâțu]], O necesitate desconsiderată: Presa românească în Basarabia, Chișinău, 1930, p.9.</ref>
Between November 14, 1935 and 1940, Gazeta Basarabiei was an independent newspaper ("Ziar popular independent de pură informație"), directed by [[Ion T. Costin]] and V. Boldescu served as editor in chief.<ref>[[Eugen Ștefan Holban]], Dicționar cronologic: Prin veacurile învolburate ale Moldovei dintre Prut și Nistru, Chișinău, 1998, 194.</ref>
