{{Infobox military conflict | conflict = Second Battle of Blida | partof = the [[French conquest of Algeria]] | image = | caption = | date = {{date|17–25 November 1830}}<ref>Histoire de l'armée et de tous les régiments, depuis les premiers temps de monarchie français jusqu'a nos jours (History of the Army and of All Regiments from Earliest Times to our Day) [https://books.google.dz/books?id=0nZkPZuQ6qsC&pg=PR58 (read online)]</ref> | place = [[Blida]] and [[Médéa]], [[Algeria]]<ref>L'Algerois rural à la fin de l'époque ottomane (1791-1830) [https://books.google.fr/books?hl=fr&id=W-5yAAAAMAAJ&d (read online)]</ref> | territory = France annexes [[Médéa]], but fails to capture [[Blida]]. | result = | combatant1 = {{flagdeco|France}} [[July Monarchy|Kingdom of France]] | combatant2 = Algerian resistance * Local [[Berbers in Algeria|Berber tribes]] | commander1 = [[Bertrand Clausel]] | commander2 = [[Mohamed Ben Zamoum]] | units1 = | units2 = | strength1 = 7,000 soldiers<ref>l'histoire de Blida (The Story of Blida) extrait de "aux échos d'Alger (from "Echos of Algiers"), numéro 45 [http://alger-roi.fr/Alger/blida/textes/3_blida_aea45.htm (read online)]</ref> | strength2 = Unknown | casualties1 = 127 killed | casualties2 = Unknown | notes = | campaignbox = {{Campaignbox French conquest of Algeria}} }}
The '''Second Battle of Blida''' was a battle between France and the local Algerian popular forces. It began on 17 November 1830 and ended eight days later on 25 November. After the failure of [[July Monarchy|France]] in the [[First Battle of Blida]], [[Louis-Auguste-Victor, Count de Ghaisnes de Bourmont|de Burman]] was relieved of his duties and General [[Bertrand Clausel]] was appointed on 17 November 1830 for a major campaign on [[Blida]] and [[Médéa]]. [[Bertrand Clausel]] conducted a massive campaign with 17,000 soldiers to invade [[Blida]] and [[Médéa]].<ref>Histoire de l'Algérie ancienne et moderne (Ancient and Modern History of Algeria) [https://books.google.dz/books?id=ilH0gaYdal8C&pg=PA581 (read online)]</ref>.
== Battle == The inhabitants of [[Blida]] refused to allow the French army into the city and a fierce battle broke out in which hundreds were killed or wounded. The French army burned the orchards surrounding the city and the inhabitants were forced to flee into the mountains. Before his departure from Blida, General [[Bertrand Clausel]] left a French garrison under the command of Colonel Roulhières<ref>Joseph et Caroline ou le berger de la Sologne. Histoire Veritable, Volumes 1-2 [https://books.google.dz/books?id=M0qKUbFc4_UC&pg=PA128 (read online)]</ref> and headed towards [[Médéa]]. He was ambushed by the Popular Resistance in a mountainous strait near [[Mouzaïa]], and 27 French soldiers were killed. Before General Clausel returned from Médéa, the French garrison in [[Blida]] managed to eliminate a French contingent of 100 soldiers near [[Boufarik]] on 25 November 1830.{{clarify |date=October 2017 |reason= Confusing/contradictory; possible mistake.}} In the face of a great resistance, General Clausel was forced to take over [[Médéa]] and withdraw completely from [[Blida]].
