[[File:Oliva in Bar.jpg|thumb|Stara Maslina]] '''Stara Maslina''' is one of the world's oldest olive trees, located near [[Stari Bar]] ([[Bar, Montenegro|City of Bar]]) in [[Montenegro]]. The tree is said to be over 2,000 years old. It is a popular tourist attraction in the country.
A side of the tree is completely burnt. According to popular folklore, a few men were playing cards next to the tree. During their game, one member accidentally threw a lit match onto the tree, and it soon went up in flames.
